Reasoning: The paper deals with natural language processing techniques such as named entity recognition and correlation analysis to measure the relationship between public persons over time. This falls under the sub-category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to extract persons' occurrence in the text, which is related to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of time series analysis and correlation measures can be associated with the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.LG) and social network analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the paper's focus on analyzing news articles can be linked to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) or systems and control (cs.SD).
